# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Type should be one of the following:
# * feat:     A new feature
# * fix:      A bug fix
# * docs:     Documentation only changes
# * style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# * refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# * perf:     A code change that improves performance
# * test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# * chore:    Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and libraries such as documentation generation
# * ci:       Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
# * build:    Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
# * revert:   Reverts a previous commit

# Scope should be the area of the codebase affected (optional):
# * backend:  Django backend changes
# * frontend: Template/view changes
# * config:   Configuration changes
# * docker:   Docker-related changes
# * celery:   Celery task changes
# * redis:    Redis-related changes
# * tests:    Test-related changes

# Subject should be:
# * imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * no period at the end
# * 50 characters or less
# * capitalized first letter

# Body should be:
# * wrapped at 72 characters
# * explain what and why vs. how
# * can use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points

# Footer should contain:
# * any breaking changes
# * reference issues that this commit closes, e.g. "Closes #123"

# Examples:
# feat(backend): add fund price tracking with Redis
#
# - Implement fetch_kweb_price Celery task
# - Add Redis integration for storing latest quotes
# - Update views to display real-time price data
#
# Closes #45

# fix(templates): resolve price display formatting issues
#
# - Fix decimal precision for price values
# - Add proper error handling for missing data
# - Improve responsive design for mobile devices

# docs(readme): update installation instructions
#
# - Add Docker Compose setup steps
# - Include environment variable configuration
# - Update Celery worker setup guide
